results.deck: Masiya was a subsidiary Japanese development studio of NCS, or Nippon Computer Systems, which primarily developed games for NEC's Turbografx-16/PC Engine.
results.description:
Overview

Masiya, which developed games for parent company NCS Corporation, is best known for the Langrisser series, the Cho Aniki series and Target Earth.
